ğŸ§ª Jenkinsfile Snippet (Declarative Pipeline)
groovy
Copy
Edit
pipeline {
  agent any

  stages {
    stage('Fetch Slot Config') {
      steps {
        script {
          def response = sh(script: "curl -s http://your-backend-domain/api/slot-options", returnStdout: true).trim()
          def config = readJSON text: response

          echo "Received slot queues:"
          config.each { queueName, groups ->
            echo "Queue: ${queueName}"
            groups.each { group ->
              echo "  -> Slots: ${group.slots}, File: ${group.file}"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }

    stage('Use Slot Config') {
      steps {
        // Example: trigger jobs or make decisions based on config
      }
    }
  }
}
ğŸ›¡ï¸ Tips for Real-World Use:

Concern	Solution
ğŸ” Secure Access	Add API key/token headers to your /api/slot-options endpoint
ğŸ“¦ Backend not public	Run Flask on same host or internal network as Jenkins
ğŸ§° Use in Bash	`curl http://...
ğŸ“‰ Error handling	Add retries or fallback logic in Jenkins if API is down
ğŸ” Logging	Log every Jenkins call to the backend for traceability
ğŸ” (Optional) Securing the API Call
Backend (Flask):
python
Copy
Edit
from flask import request, abort

@slot_bp.route('/slot-options', methods=['GET'])
def get_slot_options():
    token = request.headers.get('X-API-TOKEN')
    if token != os.getenv('JENKINS_API_TOKEN'):
        abort(403)

    config = load_slot_config()
    return jsonify(config)
